  "text": "The difference with the usual formalism of MDL is that instead of explicitly approximating the function of interest x(t) byx(t), we approximate the right-hand side function f of the dynamical system (1) bŷ f . This gives us an implicit approximate to x(t), which is produced by simulating a dynamical system from x(0) viaf rather than f . This way, we efficiently compress information about the dynamical system [CITATION_1] .",
